From 9d6e5bdb611c42d439a723135eeae6d645a7c219 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zhiyi Zhang <zzhang@codeweavers.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 22:11:13 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] winex11.drv: Return WithdrawnState when
 get_window_wm_state() fails.

KWin deletes WM_STATE property from a window when entering WithdrawnState. Please see
X11Window::exportMappingState() in the KWin source code. So when get_window_wm_state()
fails, -1 is returned before this patch. Since -1 is not a valid WM_STATE, it might cause
Wine to expect an invalid value. We also can't simply ignore the invalid -1 because we
might be expecting the WM_STATE property notify event to change to the desired state.
Treating missing WM_STATE property as WithdrawnState seems like the best way to go.

Help fix RiME(493200) sometimes fails to restore from Alt+Tab.
---
 dlls/winex11.drv/event.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c b/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
index 81f470db3dc..353cd9a9fde 100644
--- a/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
+++ b/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
@@ -1182,7 +1182,7 @@ static int get_window_wm_state( Display *display, Window window )
         XID     icon;
     } *state;
     Atom type;
-    int format, ret = -1;
+    int format, ret = WithdrawnState;
     unsigned long count, remaining;
 
     if (!XGetWindowProperty( display, window, x11drv_atom(WM_STATE), 0,
-- 
